commit 3217ea89e45a8547f8ad5c8c050a6e55ed580ec6
Author: Hampa Hug <hampa@hampa.ch>
Date:   2009-10-16 20:57:28 +0200

    macplus: Use the plain disk icon for 720K and 1440K disks

commit e524847c533ed2e4c6dfbdf2fa01499c86d6db14
Author: Hampa Hug <hampa@hampa.ch>
Date:   2009-10-16 20:56:35 +0200

    macplus: Allow better control of disk insertion at startup
    
    Each emulated disk drive now has its own insertion delay counter. The
    counter can be set in the config file or on the command line.

commit 51b226bc2ccc79f6e30ac08446f7ad2012676300
Author: Hampa Hug <hampa@hampa.ch>
Date:   2009-10-16 20:54:23 +0200

    macplus: Use the one second interrupt to check for disk insertions

commit 2aaf47951e8ffd958d1531167f0ac2266c95d353
Author: Hampa Hug <hampa@hampa.ch>
Date:   2009-10-16 20:48:19 +0200

    macplus: Fix opening the sony driver
    
    The sony open hook needs to be called *after* the extension ROM has
    allocated and initialized the sony variables. This way disks can
    be inserted immediatly after opening the driver.

commit a3707e28fd4e8da627aaecf6affcde82c87c2d55
Author: Hampa Hug <hampa@hampa.ch>
Date:   2009-10-16 19:34:04 +0200

    Remove whitespace from end of lines

commit ed17f644c2f8099e5b297d96bef6d2aa8390d466
Author: Hampa Hug <hampa@hampa.ch>
Date:   2009-10-16 19:23:53 +0200

    macplus: Put the extension ROM binary under version control
    
    The macplus extension ROM is now built only if configure is run
    with the --enable-macplus-rom option. Otherwise a pre-built
    binarys is used.

commit 9e12b6a914ca94b00f9cdf5d07d9bba5b2a245f8
Author: Hampa Hug <hampa@hampa.ch>
Date:   2009-10-16 19:21:18 +0200

    ibmpc: Put the extension ROM binary under version control
    
    The ibmpc extension ROM and the PCE EGA ROM are now built only
    if configure is run with the --enable-ibmpc-rom option. Otherwise
    pre-built binaries are used.

commit 11424d1d912251c51240b0b5f9344cad35c34580
Author: Hampa Hug <hampa@hampa.ch>
Date:   2009-10-16 13:01:38 +0200

    macplus: Add a config file option to disable the startup memory test
    
    The Macintosh Plus ROM checks if memory location 0x02ae (ROMBase)
    is initialized to 0x00400000 and if it is, it skips the startup
    memory test.

commit b260bce8825016497a358a3252799624c531389d
Author: Hampa Hug <hampa@hampa.ch>
Date:   2009-10-15 19:00:52 +0200

    macplus: Use VIA CB2 output for keyboard protocol
    
    When the keyboard wants to send a response to the VIA it needs to
    wait until the data line (CB2) goes high, which happens when CB2
    is switched from output to input in the VIA.
    
    The old code just delayed the keyboard response by 8192 clock cycles
    and hoped for the best. With this patch the state of the data line
    is actually checked.

commit a4a43c7f22eb1431269bea88ccc887e356a55455
Author: Hampa Hug <hampa@hampa.ch>
Date:   2009-10-15 19:00:01 +0200

    6522: Add support for the CB2 output

commit 945e7d9d8212328dd022e18b357fd91fce1be2c2
Author: Hampa Hug <hampa@hampa.ch>
Date:   2009-10-14 16:23:38 +0200

    macplus: Enable support for the 68010

commit 171333bd1f7754acc28fe903e7f732080e908481
Author: Hampa Hug <hampa@hampa.ch>
Date:   2009-10-14 16:20:09 +0200

    68000: Add emulation of the 68010

commit 45607c07eb0c6496828532cdc3ae29d92975bb91
Author: Hampa Hug <hampa@hampa.ch>
Date:   2009-10-14 15:49:48 +0200

    68000: Use an array of function pointers to decode EAs

commit fc66e491e4329664a6033d761e67cab81d05d9db
Author: Hampa Hug <hampa@hampa.ch>
Date:   2009-09-12 11:30:57 +0200

    e8250: Set buffer size correctly
    
    The 8250 buffers are circular queues that waste one byte in order to
    indicate the "queue full" status. In order to have the requested
    buffer capacity, the buffer size must be increased by one.

commit abdf134903d4f7d972393f7715b4c9421d51d37d
Author: Hampa Hug <hampa@hampa.ch>
Date:   2009-09-12 09:18:52 +0200

    ibmpc: Remove obsolete function pc_break()

commit 14d7a289d4a4c1990f9ce6ca89eb00f717380fe4
Author: Hampa Hug <hampa@hampa.ch>
Date:   2009-09-10 10:38:32 +0200

    ibmpc: Don't intercept PIC interrupts in the BIOS
    
    PIC interrupts (int 0x08 - 0x0f) don't need to be intercepted because
    there is no reason the emulator should ever have to handle them.

commit fe16e9abd75fef146fb753798c678ab1b2df72d7
Author: Hampa Hug <hampa@hampa.ch>
Date:   2009-09-09 19:46:06 +0200

    terminal: Ignore message "term.fullscreen" in x11 terminal
    
    The X11 terminal does not yet support fullscreen mode, but it should
    not return an error on "term.fullscreen". The message is now
    silently ignored.

commit b646635e67ca6cde65aa9db9e44e1756481de5d0
Author: Hampa Hug <hampa@hampa.ch>
Date:   2009-09-09 19:36:47 +0200

    Don't reset terminal colors
    
    Resetting the terminal colors before entering the monitor is no
    longer necessary because the colors are not changed anymore in
    the first place.

commit f3bc959e33003bad8842a97e4cd97ffd43380957
Author: Hampa Hug <hampa@hampa.ch>
Date:   2009-09-08 11:59:38 +0200

    e8237: Pulse the terminal count output

commit a75dc18cb0d59dfee9706921694d4622589e84c4
Author: Hampa Hug <hampa@hampa.ch>
Date:   2009-09-08 11:58:56 +0200

    e8237: Check all dma channels
    
    If e8237_clock() is called only occasionally, DMA channels might
    be starved.

commit 5dd2588888528996142bedd1598c6679ee5d14a6
Author: Hampa Hug <hampa@hampa.ch>
Date:   2009-09-08 04:22:01 +0200

    char-stdio: Make flushing stdio output a runtime option

commit 172bbb701592025ce30692b276069d2d3cd74d76
Author: Hampa Hug <hampa@hampa.ch>
Date:   2009-09-08 03:28:21 +0200

    char: Properly escape colons in driver options
    
    Colons in character driver options can be escaped by repeating them.
    The option parser correctly detects escaped colons but does not remove
    the second colon. This patch fixes this.

commit 568f6924ce0fa00375111da647d61c8b86518e45
Author: Hampa Hug <hampa@hampa.ch>
Date:   2009-09-07 02:26:37 +0200

    char: Add new pty character driver
    
    The pty character driver creates a new pseudo terminal and
    connects the driver to it. Optionally it can create a symlink
    to the new tty device (whose name is unpredictable).

commit 06f368d369e8b729d63cd22de01c6d2dbee0bda0
Author: Hampa Hug <hampa@hampa.ch>
Date:   2009-09-07 02:23:04 +0200

    char: Add new posix file character driver
    
    The posix file character driver reads from and writes to files using
    the read() and write() functions. Unlike the stdio character driver
    it can be used to provide input, for example using a named pipe.

commit e1507ce83ef473ed754ffe7fecf4183edbf215de
Author: Hampa Hug <hampa@hampa.ch>
Date:   2009-09-07 02:19:36 +0200

    configure: Regenerate with autoconf 2.64

commit 70efca242807488fc4a63df8eab384f05be2aca5
Author: Hampa Hug <hampa@hampa.ch>
Date:   2009-08-01 22:19:44 +0000

    e8237: Clean up
    
    No functional change, just cosmetics.

commit 44073c0953119c7d0b194651a0118356bd6eb4b4
Author: Hampa Hug <hampa@hampa.ch>
Date:   2009-08-01 22:19:08 +0000

    e8237: Fix uninitalized function pointer
    
    The hreq function pointer is never initialized. Bug found by Bill Lewis.

commit 05a240ba90ab832976c5ec6c78354b57668421ee
Author: Hampa Hug <hampa@hampa.ch>
Date:   2009-07-26 21:35:22 +0000

    ibmpc: Fix setting up the mouse
    
    If there is no "mouse" section in the config file pc->mse is left
    uninitialized. This patch makes sure that pc->mse contains either
    NULL or a valid pointer. Bug found by Bill Lewis.

commit dff9c71e6a7cd44f232b7eb0446387dec6c93724
Author: Hampa Hug <hampa@hampa.ch>
Date:   2009-07-24 21:21:21 +0000

